    slug: `kanika-gupta-shori-on-women-leadership-and-technology-transforming-indian-real-estate`,
    section: "news",
    paras: [
      `Kanika Gupta Shori highlighted how technology has been instrumental in transforming the fragmented real estate sector, addressing inefficiencies and enhancing transparency. Square Yards has led this evolution with innovations like PropVR, enabling virtual property exploration, and AI driven platforms that simplify complex processes for buyers and investors.`,
      `Kanika Gupta Shori, the Co-Founder and COO of Square Yards, highlighted the evolving dynamics of the Indian real estate sector, shedding light on the role of technology and women leadership in redefining the industry.`,
      `She also highlighted the importance of inclusivity within the workforce. She said, “At Square Yards, we consciously promote gender diversity. We give equal opportunities to men and women during recruitment and offer flexible work arrangements, childcare support and a five day workweek to help women balance work and family responsibilities. Interestingly, in our vertical home interiors, 80 percent of the workforce is comprised of women. Their creativity and intuition make them a natural fit for this space.”`,
      `When addressing biases in leadership, Shori acknowledged that the underrepresentation of women in senior roles within the real estate industry remains a significant challenge. She mentioned how women often have to contend with preconceived notions about their abilities in leadership positions, compounded by the lack of female role models in top roles.`,
      `She also reflected on her personal journey at Square Yards, highlighting the complementary roles she shares with her co-founder and husband, Tanuj Shori. While she oversees the day to day operations of the company as COO, he handles funding discussions and investor relations as CEO. She remarked that their clearly defined responsibilities and ability to balance each other's strengths have been critical to the company's success.`,
      `Looking ahead, Shori believes that women's leadership will continue to drive significant change in real estate, both in terms of decision making and professional contributions. She encouraged investors to invest more in women led businesses, pointing out the profitability and sustainability of such ventures.`,
    ],
